ðŸ–¥ï¸ Option 1: Linux (UFW)

1. Check if UFW is installed

sudo apt update
sudo apt install ufw -y

2. Enable UFW

sudo ufw enable

> Type y if it asks for confirmation.



3. Check Firewall Status

sudo ufw status

4. Block Inbound Traffic on Port 23 (Telnet)

sudo ufw deny 23

5. Test the Rule

Try to connect:

telnet localhost 23

You should see: connection refused or not allowed.


6. Allow SSH (Port 22)

sudo ufw allow 22

7. Remove the Telnet Rule

sudo ufw delete deny 23

8. Final Status

sudo ufw status numbered

ðŸ“¸ Take screenshots at each step (before, after adding rules, and testing).
